content.description: Directly to the left of Cospito's Corner, this is the hard variation of the problem. L'eggo-My-Eggo with Syrup has a brutal start, could be used as a side pull or under cling, climbers choice, it still follows the face straight up to the two hands used for the V1 variation. Again used the deep finger pocket to get your feet right. Top out is all sloper. Make sure to have crash pad and spotter if needed.
content.location: Right of trail from Rocky Hollow Picnic Area or follow trail for Tower Parking and walk toward Rocky Hollow Parking Area. Face directly to the left of Cospito's Corner. You may have to jump small stream depending on weather.

content.description: Directly to the left of Cospito's Corner. L'eggo-My-Eggo is a two hand start at about eye level. Next work hands up and throw to small finger pocket. The pocket is deep and gives you enough to work feet into good position to finish the problem. Top out is all sloper. Make sure to have crash pad and spotter if needed.

content.description: Directly to the left of Cospito's Corner, the problem has 2 variations. L'eggo-My-Eggo is a two hand start  that works its way straight up the face to the top out. L'eggo-My-Eggo with Syrup has a brutal start, could be used as a side pull or under cling, climbers choice, it still follows the face straight up. Top out is all sloper. Make sure to have crash pad and spotter if needed.
